    "comment": "Rationale: The adenosine A2B receptor is a G-protein coupled receptor that is involved in the modulation of synaptic transmission. Application of the A2B agonist BAY 60-6583 did not modify basal synaptic transmission (Fig. 1c), but caused a decrease in the paired-pulse ratio in the Schaffer collateral - commissural pathway in the hippocampus (Fig. 1d). This effect was blocked by co-application of the \"AB antagonist MRS1754 (Fig. 1e) and in A2B-KO mice (Fig. 1f).. Experimental description: Male C57/BL6 mice (10-12 weeks old) were obtained from Charles River (Barcelona, Spain) and A2BR-KO mice (Belikoff et al., 2011) were kindly donated",
